    "patch_code": "public int read(byte[] buf, int offset, int numToRead) throws IOException {\n\t\tif (numToRead <= 0) {\n\t\t\treturn 0;\n\t   \t}\n\t  \twhile (true) {\n            try {\n                return rawRead(buf, offset, numToRead);\n            } catch (IOException e) {\n            \t// The stream has probably been closed externally. We should propagate this exception instead of silencing it with an incomplete read.\n                throw e;\n            } catch (IndexOutOfBoundsException e) {\n\t\t\t\tbreak; // This should never happen since we have already checked that `offset + numToRead <= buf.length`\n        \t} finally {\n                closeCurrentEntryIfNecessary();\n            }\n       }\n      \n        return numToRead > 0 ? -1 : 0;\n}",
